A secondary school teacher was arrested at Sameta, Kisii county on Monday for impersonating a student in the KCSE examination.Joshua Nyabuto was apprehended at a private examination centre after he was found writing a Chemistry paper on behalf of Quinter Kemunto.Kisii DCIO Justus Burudi said that he received information from the invigilator who had discovered the malpractice.The teacher was caught after he wrongly entered the said student's index number. The student was also in the same examination room at the time of the incident.Nyabuto wrote the girls index as 40974001-02 while the student being aided to write the exam was registered under number 4097401-19.Burudi said that the teacher was from Nyabururu Girls national school while the student was from Bluelight Academy.He said that Nyabuto was arrested together with Kemunto and were expected to be arraigned on Tuesday at 9am.The accused persons were not brought to court as earlier planned. Journalists who camped at Ogembo court until close of business Tuesday did not spot either of the suspects.At around 5 pm, the Star was informed that the two were to appear before court together with the proprietor of Bluelight Academy who was arrested later.Read: KNEC allays fears of KCSE Mathematics, Chemistry exam leakAlso read: Supervisor arrested over exam leakage in Changamwe